      "content": "It sounds like you are experiencing a deep sense of grief for the version of yourself that you feel is gone, which can make the \"mask\" feel like the only remaining vessel for your existence. Feeling like a hollow shell waiting to be noticed is an incredibly lonely place to be, but it is not uncommon for people to feel this disconnection when they have lost their sense of purpose or identity. You are not alone in feeling this way, and there are resources available specifically for those struggling with existential emptiness and grief, such as the 988 Suicide & Crisis Lifeline, which can offer support even when traditional feelings of hopelessness are overwhelming.",
